The paper deals with the analysis of fundamental limits of statistical inference in multilayer networks, which involves linear transforms and non-linear functions. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of approximate message passing algorithms, which is a common technique in neural network research (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the existence and locations of certain phase-transitions, which is a topic in systems and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for analyzing the effects of additive Gaussian noise transforms, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
